---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { DocsBoot } from "../components/DocsBoot";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Documentation — Tonet"
  description="Tonet documentation: install, updates, code signing, and packaging."
  page="docs"
>
  <div class="docs-shell">
    <aside class="docs-sidebar" aria-label="On this page">
      <p class="docs-sidebar-title" id="docs-sidebar-title">On this page</p>
      <nav>
        <a id="docs-nav-overview" href="#docs-overview">Overview</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-map" href="#docs-map-section">Documentation map</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-install" href="#docs-install-h">Installation</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-updates" href="#docs-updates-h">In-browser updates</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-sign" href="#docs-sign-h">Authenticode (Windows)</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-deb" href="#docs-deb-h">Debian (.deb)</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-app" href="#docs-app-h">AppImage</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-cf" href="#docs-cf-h">Deploy landing</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-cdn" href="#ops-docs">CDN variables</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-product" href="#product-docs">Use cases</a>
        <a id="docs-nav-eng" href="#engineering-docs">Engineering</a>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <main class="docs-main section py-10 pb-14">
      <h1 id="docs-h1" class="text-4xl">Documentation</h1>
      <p class="lead" id="docs-lead">Guides for users, operators, and contributors — structured like a product docs portal.</p>

      <article class="card mb-5" id="docs-overview">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-overview-h">How this portal is organized</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]" id="docs-overview-p">
          Use the <strong>left outline</strong> (desktop) or jump links below on mobile. Sections follow the usual docs mental model: install → updates → packaging
          → deploy → audience → engineering tracks — similar to Docusaurus / GitBook navigation patterns, without pulling in a second SPA framework.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5" id="docs-map-section">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-map-h">Documentation map</h2>
        <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]" id="docs-map-p">Deep guides live beside the repo; this page is the entry hub with anchors into each topic.</p>
        <div class="grid">
          <a class="card no-underline hover:opacity-90" href="#product-docs">
            <h3 class="mt-0" id="docs-card-prod-h">Product and use cases</h3>
            <p id="docs-card-prod-p">Target users, deployment scenarios, and comparison framing.</p>
          </a>
          <a class="card no-underline hover:opacity-90" href="#ops-docs">
            <h3 class="mt-0" id="docs-card-ops-h">Operations and delivery</h3>
            <p id="docs-card-ops-p">CDN, release assets, update manifest, and signing flow.</p>
          </a>
          <a class="card no-underline hover:opacity-90" href="#engineering-docs">
            <h3 class="mt-0" id="docs-card-eng-h">Engineering</h3>
            <p id="docs-card-eng-p">Architecture, implementation phases, and future work tracking.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-install-h">Installation</h2>
        <p id="docs-install-p">
          See the <a class="text-tonet-link hover:underline" href="/download.html">download page</a>. The landing reads <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1"
            >version.json</code> (built from <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">crates/tonet</code> at build time) and points buttons at CDN filenames. MSI and
          tag-scoped links use versioned paths on the same CDN when published.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-updates-h">In-browser updates</h2>
        <p id="docs-updates-p">
          Tonet checks your update manifest endpoint (it does not install binaries for you). By default it checks on startup. In
          <strong>Settings (⚙)</strong> you can choose:
        </p>
        <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
          <li id="docs-updates-li1"><strong>On startup only</strong> — one check when the app opens.</li>
          <li id="docs-updates-li2"><strong>Automatic (24 h)</strong> — repeats while Tonet is running.</li>
          <li id="docs-updates-li3"><strong>Manual only</strong> — only with “Check now”.</li>
        </ul>
        <p id="docs-updates-p2">
          Settings are stored in the system config directory (for example <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">%APPDATA%\tonet</code> on Windows).
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-sign-h">Authenticode signing (Windows)</h2>
        <p id="docs-sign-p">
          For SmartScreen trust, sign MSI and EXE with a code-signing certificate (SHA-256) on Windows using <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1"
            >signtool</code> from the Windows SDK.
        </p>
        <div class="code-block pt-11">
          <button type="button" class="copy-btn" data-copy="sign-msi">Copy</button>
          <pre id="sign-msi">signtool sign /fd SHA256 /a /tr http://timestamp.digicert.com /td SHA256 Tonet-x.x.x-x64.msi
signtool sign /fd SHA256 /a /tr http://timestamp.digicert.com /td SHA256 Tonet-Setup-x.x.x-x64.exe</pre>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[0.9rem] text-[#9aa3b5]" id="docs-sign-foot">
          In CI, store the PFX in an encrypted secret and use a self-hosted runner or an action that invokes <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1"
            >signtool</code>. Never commit certificates to the repository.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-deb-h">Debian package (.deb)</h2>
        <p id="docs-deb-p">
          The script <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">packaging/debian/build-deb.sh</code> builds a <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">.deb</code> from <code
            class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">cargo build --release -p tonet</code>. Requires <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">dpkg-deb</code> (Linux).
        </p>
        <div class="code-block pt-11">
          <button type="button" class="copy-btn" data-copy="deb-build">Copy</button>
          <pre id="deb-build">cargo build --release -p tonet
./packaging/debian/build-deb.sh</pre>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-app-h">AppImage (Linux)</h2>
        <p id="docs-app-p">
          Shipping a universal AppImage requires bundling GTK/GL dependencies — consider
          <a class="text-tonet-link hover:underline" href="https://github.com/linuxdeploy/linuxdeploy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linuxdeploy</a> + the GTK plugin
          once the binary stabilizes. A dedicated workflow may land in a future release.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-cf-h">Deploy this landing (Cloudflare Workers)</h2>
        <p id="docs-cf-p1">From the <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">web/landing</code> directory:</p>
        <div class="code-block pt-11">
          <button type="button" class="copy-btn" data-copy="cf-deploy">Copy</button>
          <pre id="cf-deploy">npm ci
npm run deploy</pre>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]" id="docs-cf-p2">
          Set <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN</code> and <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID</code> in
          GitHub Actions, or run <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">wrangler login</code> locally.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5" id="ops-docs">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-cdn-h">CDN configuration (required variables)</h2>
        <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]" id="docs-cdn-p">
          To stop depending on GitHub releases endpoints, define CDN URLs in the landing build and in Tonet runtime.
        </p>
        <div class="code-block pt-11">
          <button type="button" class="copy-btn" data-copy="cdn-env">Copy</button>
          <pre id="cdn-env"># web/landing/.env(.production)
TONET_CDN_BASE_URL=https://downloads.example.com
TONET_CDN_VERSION_PATH=/version.json
TONET_SITE_DOWNLOADS_PAGE=https://downloads.example.com/

# rust build environment for Tonet app updates
TONET_UPDATE_MANIFEST_URL=https://downloads.example.com/version.json
TONET_DOWNLOADS_PAGE_URL=https://downloads.example.com/</pre>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5" id="product-docs">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-product-h">Use cases and audience</h2>
        <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
          <li id="docs-product-l1">Minimal browsing environments where deterministic behavior matters.</li>
          <li id="docs-product-l2">Teams that need transparent browser internals and release control.</li>
          <li id="docs-product-l3">Operators that prefer CDN-governed artifacts and update manifests.</li>
          <li id="docs-product-l4">Power users who want a focused browser without broad platform noise.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card mb-5" id="engineering-docs">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-eng-h">Implementation and future work</h2>
        <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
          <li id="docs-eng-l1"><strong>Current:</strong> Servo integration foundation, policy modules, and CI coverage.</li>
          <li id="docs-eng-l2"><strong>Next:</strong> broader web compatibility layers and stronger packaging parity.</li>
          <li id="docs-eng-l3"><strong>Planned:</strong> deeper conformance targets, perf budgets, and expanded platform support.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]" id="docs-eng-p">
          For detailed milestones, consult <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">TONET_VISION.md</code> and <code
            class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">docs/SERVO_INTEGRATION_CHECKLIST.md</code>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]" id="docs-eng-p2">
          Structured docs source (MkDocs-style): <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">web/landing/docs-site</code>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h2 class="mt-0" id="docs-more-h">Additional pages</h2>
        <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]" id="docs-more-p">
          Explore:
          <a class="text-tonet-link hover:underline" href="/guide.html">Using Tonet</a>, <a class="text-tonet-link hover:underline" href="/handbook.html">Handbook</a>, <a
            class="text-tonet-link hover:underline"
            href="/compare.html">Compare</a>, and <a class="text-tonet-link hover:underline" href="/roadmap.html">Roadmap</a>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <p class="mt-10 text-center text-[#9aa3b5]">
        <a class="text-tonet-link hover:underline" id="docs-footer-back" href="/">← Back to home</a>
      </p>
    </main>
  </div>
  <DocsBoot client:load />
</BaseLayout>
